$ chexa8_constrained_thermal.bdf
$ Single CHEXA8 unit cube — uniaxial constrained thermal stress (z-direction)
$
$ Geometry: 1 m × 1 m × 1 m cube
$ Material: E = 1e6 Pa, nu = 0.3, alpha = 1e-5 /°C
$ Load:     uniform T = 100 °C (ΔT = 100 °C, T_ref = 0)
$ BCs:      fix T3 of ALL eight nodes — cube cannot expand in z
$           fix T1+T2 of node 1 and T2 of node 2 — lateral rigid-body prevention
$           Cube is free to contract/expand in x and y (Poisson effect)
$
$ Hand calculation (3D, z constrained, x and y free → σ_x = σ_y = 0):
$   ε_z = 0 (kinematically enforced)
$   σ_x = σ_y = 0 (free lateral surfaces)
$   From 3D Hooke with thermal strain:
$     ε_z = [σ_z - ν*(σ_x + σ_y)] / E + α*ΔT = 0
$     σ_z = -E*α*ΔT = -1e6 * 1e-5 * 100 = -1000 Pa  (compressive)
$
$   von Mises = |σ_z| = 1000 Pa  (σ_x = σ_y = 0)
$
$   Lateral Poisson + thermal: ε_x = ε_y = -ν*σ_z/E + α*ΔT = 0.3e-3 + 1e-3 = 1.3e-3
$   Node 6 at (1,0,1): u = 1.3e-3 m  (free to move)
$
SOL 101
CEND
SUBCASE 1
  LABEL = CHEXA8 CONSTRAINED THERMAL
  LOAD = 1
  SPC = 1
  DISPLACEMENT = ALL
  STRESS = ALL
BEGIN BULK
PARAM,CSVOUT,YES
GRID,1,,0.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,2,,1.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,3,,1.0,1.0,0.0
GRID,4,,0.0,1.0,0.0
GRID,5,,0.0,0.0,1.0
GRID,6,,1.0,0.0,1.0
GRID,7,,1.0,1.0,1.0
GRID,8,,0.0,1.0,1.0
MAT1,1,1.0E6,,0.3,0.0,1.0E-5,0.0
PSOLID,1,1
CHEXA,1,1,1,2,3,4,5,6,+
+,7,8
$ Fix T3 (z) of all eight nodes — z-expansion is constrained
SPC1,1,3,1
SPC1,1,3,2
SPC1,1,3,3
SPC1,1,3,4
SPC1,1,3,5
SPC1,1,3,6
SPC1,1,3,7
SPC1,1,3,8
$ Lateral rigid-body: fix T1+T2 of node 1, T2 of node 2
SPC1,1,12,1
SPC1,1,2,2
$ Uniform temperature T = 100 °C on all nodes
TEMP,1,1,100.0
TEMP,1,2,100.0
TEMP,1,3,100.0
TEMP,1,4,100.0
TEMP,1,5,100.0
TEMP,1,6,100.0
TEMP,1,7,100.0
TEMP,1,8,100.0
ENDDATA
